<Base title="Install · astro-agent-annotate">
  <h1>Install</h1>
  <p>It's an Astro integration. Add it to your config and you're done.</p>

  <h2>1. Add the package</h2>
  <pre><code>pnpm add -D astro-agent-annotate</code></pre>

  <h2>2. Register the integration</h2>
  <pre><code>// astro.config.mjs
import &#123; defineConfig &#125; from "astro/config";
import astroAgentAnnotate from "astro-agent-annotate";

export default defineConfig(&#123;
  integrations: [astroAgentAnnotate()],
&#125;);</code></pre>
  <p>The integration self-gates to <code>astro dev</code>. <code>astro build</code> ships nothing.</p>

  <h2>3. Run dev</h2>
  <pre><code>pnpm dev</code></pre>
  <p>Look for the tag icon in the Astro dev toolbar. Hold <kbd>Alt</kbd> and click anything.</p>

  <h2>Output format</h2>
  <p>When you copy, you get markdown grouped by URL. Pages with no notes are skipped. Source paths are project-relative.</p>
  <pre><code># Annotations
_Collected 2026-05-22T19:00:00.000Z_

## `/walkthrough` — 1 note

1. **Make this button match the navbar style**
   - `src/pages/walkthrough.astro:42:7`
   - `&lt;button class="trial-cta"&gt;Sign up&lt;/button&gt;`</code></pre>
</Base>
